AWS CodeBuild is a fully managed build service — it replaces Jenkins agent/server.

Simple meaning:

Jenkins:                    CodeBuild:
────────                    ──────────
You manage EC2 server       AWS manages everything
You install Java, Maven     Pre-installed runtimes
You maintain plugins        No plugins needed
Running 24/7 costs money    Pay per build minute
You scale manually          Auto scales ✅

What CodeBuild does:

Takes your source code
        ↓
Spins up a fresh container
        ↓
Runs your buildspec.yml commands
        ↓
Build JAR ✅
Run tests ✅
Docker build ✅
Push to ECR ✅
Deploy to EKS ✅
        ↓
Container destroyed after build
        ↓
You pay only for build time ✅

CodeBuild environment:

When build starts:
  AWS spins up fresh Ubuntu container
        ↓
  Pre-installed:
    ✅ Java (corretto 8/11/17/21)
    ✅ Maven
    ✅ Docker
    ✅ AWS CLI
    ✅ Node.js
    ✅ Python
    ✅ Go
        ↓
  Runs your buildspec.yml
        ↓
  Build completes
        ↓
  Container destroyed ✅
  Nothing persists


buildspec.yml is the brain of CodeBuild:

version: 0.2

phases:
  install:       # install extra tools
  pre_build:     # login, setup
  build:         # main work
  post_build:    # deploy, notify

artifacts:       # files to save after build
reports:         # test reports
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In your pipeline:

CodePipeline orchestrates ← manager
        ↓
CodeBuild executes        ← worker
        ↓
Reads buildspec.yml       ← instructions
        ↓
Does all the actual work:
  build, test, docker, push, deploy
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
